# Trivy CVE baseline — Batch 4 / 3C.
#
# This file is the agreed allowlist for Trivy findings that we have triaged
# and accepted. The Trivy gate becomes blocking only AFTER this baseline is
# committed and the deploy.yml workflow is updated to remove
# `continue-on-error: true` from the trivy-scan job.
#
# Format: one CVE id per line (e.g. CVE-2024-12345). Inline comments allowed.
# Each entry MUST include:
#   - the CVE id
#   - severity at time of triage
#   - justification: why the finding is acceptable for this image
#   - expiry: review-by date (YYYY-MM-DD) — Trivy will surface this back to us
#
# Re-run triage every quarter. An entry past its review-by date should be
# either renewed (with fresh justification) or removed so the gate fails on it.
#
# When adding entries, prefer the narrowest scope possible (CVE id only).
# Use full path-scoped suppressions (path:CVE-...) only when a CVE truly
# affects only one component.
#
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Active suppressions (none — baseline starts clean).
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# (no entries yet — populate during the first Trivy run on dev)
